{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 16:41:43.565438", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and topology recap\\n- Intended design: 2-tier pod with two spines (AS 65100/65101), two leaves (AS 65200/65201), super-spine (AS 65000). Each leaf advertises its directly connected /24 host subnet via EBGP.\\n- Hosts under test: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) on leaf_router_0_0 and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) on leaf_router_0_1.\\n\\nEnd-to-end reachability and path\\n- Reachability: pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 0% loss, RTT avg ≈ 2.6 ms (4 probes).\\n- Traceroute pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.2: 10.0.0.1 (leaf_0_0) -> 172.16.0.32 (spine_0_0 uplink) -> 172.16.0.35 (leaf_0_1 side) -> 10.0.1.2. 4 hops, path consistent with design, low latency.\\n\\nControl plane (BGP) health\\n- All queried FRR nodes have BGP sessions Established with expected peers. No neighbors in Idle/Active. Up/Down ≈ 1 minute (recently established but stable).\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 neighbors; each reports PfxRcd=7; local connected 10.0.0.0/24; learns all other leaf /24s via BGP.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 neighbors; PfxRcd=7; local connected 10.0.1.0/24; learns others via BGP.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): neighbors to super-spine and leaves; receive expected routes; have ECMP northbound to the super-spine for remote pod /24s.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): neighbors Established to multiple spines; routes present.\\n\\nData plane (routing tables) highlights\\n- leaf_router_0_0: connected 10.0.0.0/24; all remote /24s installed as BGP via 172.16.0.32 (eth0) only.\\n- leaf_router_0_1: connected 10.0.1.0/24; all remote /24s installed via 172.16.0.34 (eth0) only.\\n- spine routers: show ECMP to remote /24s across both super-spine links (two next-hops installed).\\n- Super-spine: routes present; some destinations installed via a single next-hop (not used for intra-pod traffic between pc_0_0 and pc_0_1).\\n\\nDetected anomalies or noteworthy deviations\\n1) Lack of ECMP at the leaves despite multiple equal EBGP paths:\\n- Evidence: On both leaves, all remote /24 routes are installed with a single next-hop (leaf_0_0 via 172.16.0.32; leaf_0_1 via 172.16.0.34).\\n- Contrast: leaf BGP summaries show multiple neighbors each advertising all needed prefixes (PfxRcd=7), implying multiple equal-cost candidates exist.\\n- Impact: No current connectivity issue; however, traffic from the leaves uses only one spine uplink rather than load-balancing/redundancy via ECMP. This is suboptimal behavior relative to common Clos design expectations but not an outage.\\n\\n2) Topology scope discrepancy versus provided description:\\n- Observation: Devices report additional BGP neighbors (e.g., AS 65202/65203, etc.) and extra inter-router subnets beyond the minimal two-spine/two-leaf pod described.\\n- Impact: No functional issue for the hosts under test; but the lab appears to be a larger fabric than the simplified topology description.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- No device or link failure detected. All links used in the pc_0_0 <-> pc_0_1 path are operational with low latency and 0% loss.\\n- The only “anomalous” behavior (lack of ECMP) is localized to leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 forwarding decisions.\\n\\nLikely root cause(s)\\n- ECMP not enabled or not selected on the leaves for EBGP-learned equal-cost paths (e.g., absence of multipath configuration or bestpath policy causes single-best-path selection). This explains single next-hop installations on leaves despite multiple equal candidates. This is a configuration/design choice rather than a fault.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Fabric health: Good. End-to-end connectivity between the given hosts is normal with stable and correctly resolved paths.\\n- Control plane: All BGP sessions are up and exchanging expected prefixes.\\n- Data plane: Forwarding is correct; minor suboptimality at leaves due to single-path selection.\\n- No active failures identified. The only noteworthy deviation is the lack of ECMP at leaf routers, attributable to configuration/policy rather than a device fault., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='8eb131ec-034c-46b0-a91a-aeaf17d4d447'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
